name: 2-Methoxyethanol
Reason: 2-Methoxyethanol is a derivative of ethanol, which has a melting point of -114.1°C. The addition of a methoxy group (OCH3) to ethanol increases the molecular weight and introduces a polar ether functionality, which can increase the melting point due to hydrogen bonding and dipole-dipole interactions. The methoxy group is estimated to increase the melting point by approximately 20°C.
